As the culinary & culture editor of @lapalmemagazine. I have the distinct honor of supporting and sharing with our readers  incredible restaurants and events from around the globe. On our trip to Puerto Rico, our tour guide suggested @cactupr located at the base of the town square in Arecibo and just minutes away from the Atlantic ocean. This  unique vegan based restaurant is a hidden gem worth traveling to! My friends and I kicked off our meal with a fresh melón and rum cocktail garnished with edible marigold. The flavor was an out of body experience. This delicious hand crafted cocktail, was followed up with Oregano Bruno Tapas which encompassed homemade bread, their in-house pesto, balsamic tomatoes, mozzarella, and micro greens. It was almost too beautiful too eat. (Mind you it was gone within minutes.) Lastly we wrapped up with Tacos de Berenjena. Flash fried eggplant, lettuce, purple cabbage, pico de gallo, and spicy mayo. The proprietors of Cactú are very welcoming and you feel at home the moment you sit down at their intimate outdoor seating area. Be sure to stop by the next time you're in Puerto Rico!

🦜Welcome to the jungle baby 🐍

As we step into 2023, be bold enough and daring enough to believe in the abundant good that has been prepared for you! Cheers to an amazing new year my friends! 💛

🌟 Embracing the Eternal Light of a Dear Friend 🌟

It is with heavy hearts and profound sadness that I share the news of the passing of, Jasmine Monica Midkiff, @jassymid on July 24th. 💔🕊️ Her departure has left a void in our lives, but her memory will forever be a guiding light, inspiring us to live with love and unity, just as she did.

Jasmine was not just a best friend to many; she was a soul sister who touched the lives of many with her radiant spirit and unwavering faith. Her love knew no bounds, and her compassionate heart embraced everyone with open arms, making each of us feel valued and cherished.

As we mourn the loss of our dear friend, let us also celebrate the beautiful moments we shared with her. Jazzy's laughter was contagious, her wisdom was profound, and her presence was a beacon of hope. 🌺✨

I invite you to honor Jasmine's legacy by embodying the principles she lived by - to love unconditionally, to see the divine spark in each other, and to be a source of comfort and healing to those in need. May we carry her light within us and spread it far and wide, creating ripples of love in the world around us. 🌊❤️ 🌍 

Rest peacefully, my dear sweet Jasmine, in the arms of the Beloved. Your spirit lives on in the love you shared and the countless lives you touched. We are forever grateful for the gift of your friendship and sisterhood. Love you so very much Jassy, Namaste. 🙏🏼 

#InLovingMemory #RememberingJasmine #EmbracingLove #RestInPeaceDearFriend #BelovedSoul

It's a been a week since I returned to @thewoodscampground from an unexpected trip to Virginia. Reuniting with loved ones in way that we never imagined in the end. I'm still processing what happened and giving thanks for all the memories that my chosen family and I share together. This morning I took this photo here at camp. It's the spitting image of our childhood. A modest dock, a yellow paddle boat, and a lake which served as our backyard, playground, and an escape from reality. I've spent a fair amount of time on reflection since my return. But most importantly savoring and celebrating the present moment. Being here has always inspired me in profound ways. I can't wait to share with you what I've been working on since my arrival. So I invite you to watch this space! 😊I'd like to kick off this week with a quote by the late Charles Fillmore co-founder of the Unity movement "I fairly sizzle with zeal, energy, and enthusiasm; eager to do that which ought to be done by me today." Have a great Monday #instafam

Collecting paintings has been a passion on mine since I was in my early 20's. My father and I would rummage through thrift stores, flea markets, garage sales, etc. all over South Florida. It's a fond memory I have of him and I. Yesterday I stumbled across this beautiful painting at @thepoverellocenterinc thrift store in Wilton Manors. Where much of my newer pieces have come from. Many thanks to the generous donors who donate to the artwork to the organization. It's now hanging in my sitting room. I think my Dad would be proud of this find. It's always a mystery how the art came about, why it ended up at the thrift store, and who the artist was/is. I am currently obsessed with how large the artist signed their name on the bottom right corner. I think they were quite proud of this piece. I'm now quite proud to share it with the 🌍.

🍂🍁 Embracing the Magic of Fall 🍁🍂

As the crisp autumn air envelops us and the leaves begin their graceful descent, I'm reminded of the beauty that is the first days of fall. 🍂🌲
@thewoodscampground has become my sanctuary, my refuge, and my annual tradition. It symbolizes the closing of an old chapter and the warm embrace of something new, something full of hope and promise. 📖✨
Each year, as the season changes, I eagerly anticipate my closing day canoe ride, a cherished ritual that brings me immeasurable joy. 🛶💫
This year, I had the honor of sharing this experience with a very special companion, Finlay. 🐾💕 Finlay, my rescue dog from @adoptmiamipets has brought an abundance of love and light into my life since the day we met. 🐶❤️
Together, we paddled along the calm waters, savoring every moment, every rustle of leaves, and every whispered promise of the coming winter. 🍁🍂
It's these simple moments that remind us of the beauty in change and the importance of treasuring the present. 🍁📷🧡
As we welcome the autumn season with open hearts, let us all find our own special moments of reflection and gratitude. 🍂✨
May this fall be a season of renewal, connection, and embracing the beauty in every day. 🍂🍃✨

🍷🌄 An Afternoon of Bliss at Blue Ridge Winery 🌄🍷

I had the privilege of spending the day at the stunning @blueridgewinery in the heart of the foothills of the Lehigh Valley, accompanied by my dear friend @jhonny_lara1 🍇🍕

We indulged in exquisite wine tastings, explored the lush vineyards, and devoured their famous coal oven pizza, which is a culinary masterpiece in its own right. 🍕🍇🔥

But what truly made this day unforgettable was the laughter. We laughed until our ribs hurt and our faces turned shades of crimson that matched Blue Ridges famous "Renegade" red blend wine. 🤣❤️🍷

It was a beautiful reminder to savor each moment, cherish every hearty chuckle, and most importantly, to finish the damn bottle! 🍾🤘

Here's to celebrating life, to exploring new horizons, and to holding on to the friendships that make every sip of wine taste even sweeter.🥂💫

Cheers to the @blueridgewinery for your kind hospitality, to dear friends, and to the delicious, laughter-filled moments that remind us why life is worth toasting to! 🍷🌟
